<h3>
<span style="color: rgb(51, 153, 255); ">Department: Web Development/ UX &amp; Conversion</span></h3>
<p>
The User Experience and Conversion team is the force behind gathering user insights, understanding personas and designing inspiring interface to engage users. We live by the mantra &quot;<em>Focus on the user and all else will follow</em>&quot;. We indulge in good visual designs and love spreading stories of a great user experience. Collaborating closely with copywriters and Web developers, we create great-looking websites that will deliver a compelling user experience.</p>
<h3>
<span style="color: rgb(51, 153, 255); ">Role: Interaction Design</span></h3>
<p>
An Interaction Designer is more than just a front-end Visual Designer for the Web. Aesthetics comes after functionality. In clickTRUE, we stress on data-driven design, which requires you to look at user motives and dataset objectively, before working your magic to create inspiring user interfaces. If you&#39;re a critical thinker with a good design sense, a strong background in CSS/HTML, and an eye for making things better, this job is for you.</p>
<h3>
<span style="color: rgb(51, 153, 255); ">Responsibilities</span></h3>
<div>
<div>
<ul>
<li>
Collaborate with various stakeholders to optimize ease-of-use, a consistent look and feel, and a conversion-driven design.</li>
<li>
Develop high level and/or detailed storyboards, mockups and prototypes to effectively communicate interaction and design ideas.</li>
<li>
Conduct ongoing research of web-based user interface development best practices.</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
<h3>
<span style="color: rgb(51, 153, 255); ">Requirements</span></h3>
<ul>
<li>
<strong>Passion in pursuing the latest design trends</strong><em>&nbsp;(If you love <a href="http://www.smashingmagazine.com/" target="_blank">Smashing Magazine</a> and Six Revisions, you should be a good fit!)</em></li>
<li>
Experience in web design, with specific expertise with web-based applications, email newsletters and web banners.</li>
<li>
Fluency with web standards and technologies, including: CSS, HTML, JavaScript, Ajax and Flash.</li>
<li>
Ability to communicate effectively in writing, verbally and as a presenter</li>
<li>
Self-motivated and self-managed with a high degree of analytical ability and intellectual curiosity</li>
<li>
Strong attention to detail, and a commitment to delivering highly-polished web-based mockups under tight time constraints</li>
</ul>
<h3>
Experience</h3>
<p>
At least 3 years experience in designing web interfaces.</p>
